intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to:
Demonstrate familiarity with the relevant programming environment; 
Perform simple programming using primitive data types and objects;
Implement simple algorithms using repetition and conditional execution;
Develop well-structured programs in Python, employing suitable elementary algorithms and data structures as required;
Write maintainable, robust, reliable, and reusable code, together with concise and informative documentation;
Provide evidence of program correctness through thorough testing.
